<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-10-10T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-10-10T11:00:00-05:00" n="392" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d392">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">500.C1112/62: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Geneva</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gilbert</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-10-10T17:00:00+01:00">October
                                    10, 1936—5 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received October 10—3:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>431. In introducing the report and resolutions of the Second
                                Committee<note n="44" xml:id="d392fn44">Adopted October 9; see
                                League of Nations, <hi rend="italic">Official Journal</hi>, Special
                                Supplement No. 157, pp. 86 and 97.</note> which were approved by the
                            Assembly this afternoon in substantially the form reported in the
                            Consulate’s telegrams 426, October 9, 8 p.m., and 425, October 9, 2
                                p.m.,<note n="45" xml:id="d392fn45">Neither printed.</note> Spinasse
                            made a strong plea for the removal of the obstacles to trade.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Gilbert</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>